@node BUGS "What is wrong"

                           Known Bugs and Problems
                           -----------------------

     There are a few points that you should note:

     1. Volume / device names set in the interface cannot have spaces, ie

        use RAM: instead of Ram Disk:

     2. If your MPEG contains AUDIO data then Mpeg2Anim will try and strip
        out as much of the AUDIO as possible, if it comes accross an error
        then it will converts as far as it has got.

     3. The CRASH feature doesn't work if either the SWAP area is set to RAM:
        as the frames are lost on a reset or if the skip features is used.

     4. The SWAP area must be a VOLUME not a DIRECTORY 

     


                                @{"Back to Main Menu"LINK MAIN}

@endnode

