@node LEG "legal"

                                  Legal Stuff
                                  -----------

                    You use this program at your own risk.

    MPEG2ANIM uses a few other PD programs to run, they are;

    VAREXX     - the great code that makes GUI's for AREXX programs.

    GFXCON     - the part that converts the frames, the full archive of
                 gfxcon is contained in the MISC directory.

    MP         - a public domain mpeg player, the distribution archive can
                 be found in the MISC directory.

    BUILDANIM  - the part the complies the ANIM file, again the full
                 distribution archive is in the MISC directory.

    EXECREXX   - PD REXX compiler

    REND24     - Shareware image converter


    All of the FULL distribution archives of the above can be found in the
    archive directory. Most are Freeware but a few are email/shareware,
    please show your support for the authors of these great Amiga programs.




